      <hedline>
        <hl1>Treatment for Minor Injuries</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Hal Strelnick letter on January 30 Cases column agrees with diagnosis of Gina Kolata's foot pain</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Regarding Gina Kolata's ''When the Simple Solution is the Right One'' (Cases, Jan. 30), often the simple physician is the right one, too. Unlike most general internists, family physicians are trained to diagnose and treat minor injuries based on careful histories and physical exams. Tendon sheath injections have saved many of my patients from expensive diagnostic and painful surgical procedures. After seeing many orthopedic surgeons without relief, several said of the simple injection, ''Doc, it's a miracle!''</p>
        <p>Hal Strelnick, M.D.  Bronx</p>
      </block>
